==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frequent
<hw>Fre"quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frequens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, crowded, frequent, akin to
<ets>farcire</ets> to stuff: cf. F. <ets>fr⟦eacute⟧quent</ets>. Cf.
<er>Farce</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Often to be met
with; happening at short intervals; often repeated or occurring; <as>as,
<ex>frequent</ex> visits</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Frequent</xex> feudal
towers.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Addicted to any course of conduct; inclined to
indulge in any practice; habitual; persistent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He has been loud and <qex>frequent</qex> in declaring himself
hearty for the government.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Full; crowded; thronged.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is C⟦ae⟧sar's will to have a <qex>frequent</qex> senate.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Often or commonly reported.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is <qex>frequent</qex> in the city he hath subdued⟦br⟧
The Catti and the Daci.</q> <rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frequent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Frequent
<hw>Fre*quent"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Frequented</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Frequenting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>frequentare</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>fr⟦eacute⟧quenter</ets>. See <er>Frequent</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To visit often; to resort to often
or habitually; <as>as, to <ex>frequent</ex> a tavern</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>frequented</qex> the court of Augustus.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make full; to fill.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With their sighs the air⟦br⟧
<qex>Frequenting</qex>, sent from hearts contrite.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frequentable</ent>⟦br⟧
